  "body": "Closes #1524\r\nFixes #1026\r\n\r\nThis carries #1524 but moves the image creation to the client and out of `ctr`.\r\n\r\nIt allows the user to input an image name for the checkpoint or else generates the checkpoint image name with the name of the task and timestamp.\r\n\r\n```\r\nsudo ctr images ls                                                                                                                  \r\nREF                                                TYPE                                                      DIGEST                                                                  SIZE     PLATFORM    LABELS                        \r\ndocker.io/library/redis:alpine                     application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.list.v2+json sha256:081fb9b298b9d703de4db5441e456973f1346572cb22927cc78caa5c7964b5b7 10.0 MiB linux/amd64 -                             \r\ndocker.io/library/registry:2.5                     application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.list.v2+json sha256:9a81c5445ea6f2559a430b1f0fae61ef906ed2ddb953c1b49bc5fee9af5c6480 10.7 MiB linux/amd64 -                             \r\ndocker.io/library/registry:latest                  application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.list.v2+json sha256:0f8fe61fa337b8ef02217702ba979b47a7d68717d4628f31592ebff85915f3ba 10.2 MiB linux/amd64 -                             \r\nio.containerd/checkpoint/redis:10-17-2017-16:54:30 application/vnd.oci.image.index.v1+json                   sha256:24c4cecbd1fe75681c5767ef7e510f08e27cf30d2c4e87ea07b3af058c287a02 16.3 MiB linux/amd64 containerd.io/checkpoint=true \r\n\r\n```",
